PROBLEM TO POSE (turn ONLY this into the word problem; keep every number exactly as written):
- Function: y = cos({{ innerLatex }})
- Ask the student to state the basic properties of this cosine function from its graph —
  domain, range, parity (even/odd), and period — and to describe its interval of decrease.

=== INTERNAL (guidance for you only — never show, restate, paraphrase, number, or hint any of this to the student) ===
- Key facts to recall: the cosine is defined for all x, its graph stays within a bounded
  horizontal strip, it is symmetric about the OY axis (the one even basic trig function),
  and its wave repeats after a fixed interval; a coefficient k inside the function
  compresses the graph, dividing the period and the decrease interval by k; it decreases
  over one half-period and rises over the other.
- Render all math as LaTeX inside $...$ (e.g. $y = \cos\left({{ innerLatex }}\right)$).
- Do NOT state or hint at the answer: the domain, range, parity, period, or which
  intervals are decreasing must NOT be given to the student.
